  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "1. Tool Overview",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Description",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Auditd (Audit Daemon) is a Linux-based auditing tool used to monitor and log system activity. It is a key component of the Linux Auditing System and helps security professionals, system administrators, and forensic analysts track events such as unauthorized access, policy violations, and system modifications. Auditd provides real-time monitoring of files, users, and processes to ensure compliance with security policies and regulatory requirements.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Auditd can be configured to log specific activities, generate alerts for suspicious behavior, and integrate with SIEM (Security Information and Event Management) solutions. Its flexibility and detailed logging capabilities make it an essential tool for system hardening and incident response.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Category",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Auditd is useful in multiple security phases:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Category",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Role",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "System Monitoring",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Logging user and system activities",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Intrusion Detection",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Detecting unauthorized access and policy breaches",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Compliance Auditing",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Ensuring adherence to security policies",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Forensics",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Investigating security incidents",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Developer/Maintainer",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Auditd is developed and maintained by the Linux community, with contributions from Red Hat and other organizations. It is included in most Linux distributions as a core security tool.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "License",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Auditd is open-source and distributed under the GNU General Public License (GPL), allowing free use, modification, and distribution.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Official Resources",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Official Documentation: https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-us/red_hat_enterprise_linux/",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "GitHub Repository: https://github.com/linux-audit/audit-userspace",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Man Page: https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man8/auditd.8.html",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "2. Installation Guide",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "System Requirements",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Auditd is compatible with most Linux distributions, including:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Ubuntu/Debian",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "CentOS",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Fedora",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Arch Linux",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Hardware Requirements:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Minimum 1 GHz processor",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "512 MB RAM (recommended 2 GB for high-traffic servers)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "At least 50 MB of disk space (more for extensive logs)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Installation Methods",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Ubuntu/Debian:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sudo apt update",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sudo apt install auditd audispd-plugins",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "RHEL/CentOS/Fedora:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sudo yum install audit audit-libs",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Arch Linux:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sudo pacman -S audit",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Verification",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "To confirm Auditd is installed correctly, run:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "auditctl -v",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "3. Basic Configuration",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Initial Setup",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Auditd runs as a background service and starts automatically upon installation. It uses rule-based configuration to define which activities should be monitored.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Configuration Files",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Main Configuration: /etc/audit/auditd.conf",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Rules Configuration: /etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Common Configuration Options",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "To set the maximum log file size, edit /etc/audit/auditd.conf:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "log_file = /var/log/audit/audit.log",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "max_log_file = 10",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "max_log_file_action = ROTATE",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "To apply configuration changes, restart the service:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sudo systemctl restart auditd",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Defining Audit Rules",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "To monitor a specific file or directory:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "auditctl -w /etc/passwd -p wa -k passwd_changes",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-w /etc/passwd → Watch file",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-p wa → Monitor write and attribute changes",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-k passwd_changes → Tag rule with a key",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "To make rules persistent, add them to /etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "4. Core Functionality",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Key Features",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Process Monitoring – Track commands executed by users.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "File Access Auditing – Monitor access to sensitive files.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "User Activity Logging – Record login attempts and privilege escalations.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Network Connection Auditing – Log network-related system calls.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Policy Compliance – Ensure adherence to security regulations.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "SIEM Integration – Send logs to external monitoring tools.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Command Structure",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "auditctl [options] <rule>",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Common Commands",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Purpose",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Command",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Explanation",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "View active rules",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "auditctl -l",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Lists current audit rules",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Monitor a file",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "auditctl -w /etc/shadow -p wa -k auth",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Watches for write and attribute changes",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Monitor user login",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "auditctl -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S execve -k user_login",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Logs executed commands",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "View audit logs",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "ausearch -k auth",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Searches logs for the \"auth\" key",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Generate audit report",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "aureport -l",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Displays a summary of login-related events",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Remove all rules",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "auditctl -D",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Deletes all active audit rules",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Example: Monitoring Unauthorized File Access",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Add a rule to watch /etc/passwd: auditctl -w /etc/passwd -p wa -k passwd_changes",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Check if the rule is active: auditctl -l",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Review logs for modifications: ausearch -k passwd_changes",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Use cases:-1.1 User Activity Monitoringaim:-Monitor account activity, session logging for anomaliesExpected output:-Real-time activity monitoring.Tool:- auditd",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Step-1 Install & Start auditd",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sudo apt update && sudo apt install auditd -y",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sudo systemctl enable --now auditd",
    "images": [
      "image2.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Step -2 Set Audit Rules",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "auditctl -w /var/log/auth.log -p wa -k user_logins",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "auditctl -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S execve -k command_execution",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "auditctl -w /etc/sudoers -p wa -k privilege_escalation",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "auditctl -w /etc/passwd -p wa -k user_modifications",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image10.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Step-3 Make Rules Persistent",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sudo nano /etc/audit/rules.d/user_activity.rules",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "sudo augenrules --load && sudo systemctl restart auditd",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image7.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Step-4 View Logs",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "ausearch -k user_logins",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "ausearch -k command_execution --interpret",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "tail -f /var/log/audit/audit.log",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": [
      "image3.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Step-5 analysis",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "I'll analyze this auditd log for account activity and session logging anomalies.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Looking at the logs, I can see several key activities:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
